chunks.body:
Syntax: entity EntityName { FieldName fieldType } or with table: entity EntityName (table_name) { ... }
Common field types: String, Integer, Long, Boolean, Float, Double, BigDecimal, LocalDate, Instant, ZonedDateTime, Duration, UUID, byte[], AnyBlob, ImageBlob, TextBlob.
Example:
entity Customer {
  firstName String required
  lastName String
  email String unique
  balance BigDecimal
  createdAt Instant
}

Declare with: relationship RelationshipType { FromEntity{fieldName} to ToEntity{fieldName} [with javadoc("...")] }
Types: OneToMany, ManyToOne, ManyToMany, OneToOne.
Example:
relationship ManyToOne {
  Order{customer} to Customer
}
relationship OneToMany {
  Customer{order} to Order{customer}
}
ManyToMany uses join entity or implicit mapping depending on generator; prefer explicit owning side field names.

Optional top-level block:
application {
  config {
    baseName myapp
    applicationType monolith
    packageName com.example
    authenticationType jwt
    databaseType sql
    devDatabaseType h2Disk
    prodDatabaseType postgresql
  }
}
Only use keys you need; invalid keys break import.
